aiSLCSysCfg.name: aiSLCSysCfg
aiSLCSysCfg.contactinfo: Engineering MIB Administrator Postal: Applied Innovation Inc. 5800 Innovation Drive Dublin, Ohio 43017-3271 Tel: 614-798-2000 Fax: 614-798-1770 Email: snmp@aiinet.com
aiSLCSysCfg.description: MIB module for SLC system parameters.

aislcscSystemPrompt.name: aislcscSystemPrompt
aislcscSystemPrompt.description: Prompt for login shells. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcscShellMinLogLevel.name: aislcscShellMinLogLevel
aislcscShellMinLogLevel.description: Minimum message severity which will be logged to a shell connection.

aislcscFtpPort.name: aislcscFtpPort
aislcscFtpPort.description: TCP port for accepting FTP connections.

aislcscTelnetPort.name: aislcscTelnetPort
aislcscTelnetPort.description: TCP port for accepting Telnet connections.

aiSLCSysCfgManagerTable.name: aiSLCSysCfgManagerTable
aiSLCSysCfgManagerTable.description: Table of IP addresses to which SNMP traps will be sent, indexed by an integer.

aislcscManagerIndex.name: aislcscManagerIndex
aislcscManagerIndex.description: Index into this table of SNMP managers.

aislcscManagerAddress.name: aislcscManagerAddress
aislcscManagerAddress.description: SNMP manager IP address. 0.0.0.0 indicates an unused entry.

aislcscManagerTrapPort.name: aislcscManagerTrapPort
aislcscManagerTrapPort.description: SNMP manager trap port destination number.

aislcscReadCommunity.name: aislcscReadCommunity
aislcscReadCommunity.description: SNMP community string for read-only access.

aislcscWriteCommunity.name: aislcscWriteCommunity
aislcscWriteCommunity.description: SNMP community string for read-write access.

aislcsctl1SourceID.name: aislcsctl1SourceID
aislcsctl1SourceID.description: TL1 source identifier. Maximum length is 20 characters.

aislcsctl1LogonRequired.name: aislcsctl1LogonRequired
aislcsctl1LogonRequired.description: Indicates whether or not an ACT-USER command is required for TL1 access.

aislcsctl1NumBadLogons.name: aislcsctl1NumBadLogons
aislcsctl1NumBadLogons.description: The number of failed TL1 logons that have occurred since the last successful logon.

aislcscExtProbeStatus.name: aislcscExtProbeStatus
aislcscExtProbeStatus.description: This is the state of the external temperature probe. It is either available or unavailable.

aislcscExtLowThreshCelsius.name: aislcscExtLowThreshCelsius
aislcscExtLowThreshCelsius.description: The lower threshold for the external temperature probe, in degrees Celsius. When the temperature drops below this value, an SNMP trap is sent.

aislcscExtHighThreshCelsius.name: aislcscExtHighThreshCelsius
aislcscExtHighThreshCelsius.description: The upper threshold for the external temperature probe, in degrees Celsius. When the temperature rises above this value, an SNMP trap is sent.

aislcscIntProbeStatus.name: aislcscIntProbeStatus
aislcscIntProbeStatus.description: This is the state of the internal temperature probe. It is either available or unavailable.

aislcscIntLowThreshCelsius.name: aislcscIntLowThreshCelsius
aislcscIntLowThreshCelsius.description: The lower threshold for the internal temperature probe, in degrees Celsius. When the temperature drops below this value, an SNMP trap is sent.

aislcscIntHighThreshCelsius.name: aislcscIntHighThreshCelsius
aislcscIntHighThreshCelsius.description: The upper threshold for the internal temperature probe, in degrees Celsius. When the temperature rises above this value, an SNMP trap is sent.

aislcscExceededThresholdValue.name: aislcscExceededThresholdValue
aislcscExceededThresholdValue.description: The temperature sent with the last trap (Celsius).

aiSLCSysCfgKeepAliveTable.name: aiSLCSysCfgKeepAliveTable
aiSLCSysCfgKeepAliveTable.description: Table of IP addresses which will be pinged periodically.

aislcscKeepAliveAddress.name: aislcscKeepAliveAddress
aislcscKeepAliveAddress.description: IP address of network element to ping. 0.0.0.0 indicates an unused entry.

aislcscKeepAliveInterval.name: aislcscKeepAliveInterval
aislcscKeepAliveInterval.description: Time between successive pings of the network element. Allowable values are 5 to 600 seconds.

aislcscKeepAliveWarningText.name: aislcscKeepAliveWarningText
aislcscKeepAliveWarningText.description: Message sent in SNMP trap when the network element stops responding to pings. Maximum length is 64 characters.

aislcscKeepAliveOKText.name: aislcscKeepAliveOKText
aislcscKeepAliveOKText.description: Message sent in SNMP trap when the network element begins responding to pings after a period of unresponsiveness. Maximum length is 64 characters.

aislcscKeepAliveCommStat.name: aislcscKeepAliveCommStat
aislcscKeepAliveCommStat.description: Determines the current communication status between the system and the target equipment. If the target equipment does not respond to pings, this object will be set to lost(3). This object will be set to disabled(1) if no IP address is configured.

aislcscActiveConfigName.name: aislcscActiveConfigName
aislcscActiveConfigName.description: Name of the active configuration file. Maximum length is 255 characters; additional restrictions are system-dependent.

aislcscActiveConfigCRC.name: aislcscActiveConfigCRC
aislcscActiveConfigCRC.description: 32-bit CRC of the active configuration file.

aislcscSoftwareUpdateName.name: aislcscSoftwareUpdateName
aislcscSoftwareUpdateName.description: To update the system software, set this object to the name of the new image file, and monitor aislcscSoftwareUpdateStatus until it changes to ok(1) or error(3). If the update succeeds, the new software will be used after the system is rebooted. Maximum length is 255 characters; additional restrictions are system-dependent.

aislcscSoftwareUpdateStatus.name: aislcscSoftwareUpdateStatus
aislcscSoftwareUpdateStatus.description: See aislcscSoftwareUpdateName for a description of how to use this object. ready(1) -- ready to update software (read-write) inProgress(2) -- update is in progress (read-only) ok(3) -- update completed successfully (read-only) error(4) -- update failed (read-only)

aislcscResetSystem.name: aislcscResetSystem
aislcscResetSystem.description: When read, this object is always none(1). Setting none(1) has no effect. Setting coldStart(2) reboots the system.

aislcscDiscPowerSupplyStatus.name: aislcscDiscPowerSupplyStatus
aislcscDiscPowerSupplyStatus.description: Status of the power supply. okay(1) or trouble(2). When the SLC is booted, this indicates okay(1) until the software determines the correct status.

aislcscMib2ReadCommunity.name: aislcscMib2ReadCommunity
aislcscMib2ReadCommunity.description: SNMP community string for read-only access with mib-2 view.

aislcscOverallAlarmSeverity.name: aislcscOverallAlarmSeverity
aislcscOverallAlarmSeverity.description: Current overall alarm severity (0-7). This value can be set at the user's discretion, but will be overwritten when the next alarm is generated.

aislcscTimeZone.name: aislcscTimeZone
aislcscTimeZone.description: The current Time Zone of the system in the following format: <+|->HH:MM, where HH is the number of hours and MM is the number of minutes. <+/-> specifies the East/West direction. For example, EDT would be displayed as: -05:00

aislcscDayLightSaving.name: aislcscDayLightSaving
aislcscDayLightSaving.description: Indicates whether Daylight saving is enabled.

aislcscSntpPoll.name: aislcscSntpPoll
aislcscSntpPoll.description: Indicates whether the SNTP client is enabled on this system.

aislcscNtpServerAddr1.name: aislcscNtpServerAddr1
aislcscNtpServerAddr1.description: IP address of the primary NTP Server

aislcscNtpServerAddr2.name: aislcscNtpServerAddr2
aislcscNtpServerAddr2.description: IP address of the secondary NTP Server

aislcscStandaloneStatus.name: aislcscStandaloneStatus
aislcscStandaloneStatus.description: standalone(1): The card is operating standalone (no external CLC). nonStandalone(2): The card is operating as a line card with a CLC.

aislcscShellPromptTimeout.name: aislcscShellPromptTimeout
aislcscShellPromptTimeout.description: Time in minutes before an idle shell is automatically closed. 0 indicates no timeout.

aislcscDestMenuBreakSeq.name: aislcscDestMenuBreakSeq
aislcscDestMenuBreakSeq.description: Sequence of characters to exit a connection made from the destination menu.
